gxde-k9 (2.0.0) UNRELEASED; urgency=low

  * Chocker TUI: menus now remember the previously selected item when
    returning from a sub-menu (main menu, task list, action submenu,
    logs submenu and log browser) via whiptail/dialog --default-item.
  * Chocker TUI: add and import no longer offer a system-scope picker;
    K9 is a user-space service manager and configurations are created
    user-side only from the TUI. The CLI retains --system for packagers.
  * Update help text: only enable/disable/remove require privilege
    escalation for system-scope tasks; add/import create user configs.

 -- shenmo <shenmo@spark-app.store>  Thu, 23 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0800

gxde-k9 (1.9.3) UNRELEASED; urgency=low

  * Chocker: start/stop/restart no longer require privilege escalation for
    system-scope tasks; only enable/disable/remove (and add/import) modify
    system config files and need sudo/pkexec.
  * Update help text to clarify which operations require privilege escalation
    and redefine "system" as user-space services installed system-wide.

 -- shenmo <shenmo@spark-app.store>  Thu, 23 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0800

