gxde-k9 (1.8.0) UNRELEASED; urgency=low

  * gxde-k9-chocker: replace number-driven `select` menus with a full TUI
    based on whiptail/dialog (arrow-key navigation, checklist, inputbox,
    yesno, scrollable textbox). Bumped chocker version to 1.1.0.
  * chocker: add batch-remove (multi-select checklist) and unified
    "pick log task" picker reused across logs show/export.
  * chocker: show config and logs inside a scrollable textbox; list/status
    output is now viewed in-app instead of dumping to terminal.
  * chocker: require_tui() checks for whiptail/dialog at startup and prints
    install hints for Debian/GXDE, Arch and Termux when missing;
    non-interactive subcommands still work without a TUI.
  * control: add "whiptail | dialog" to Depends.

 -- shenmo <shenmo@spark-app.store>  Mon, 21 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0800

gxde-k9 (1.7.0) UNRELEASED; urgency=low

  * Add per-task logging (categorized under ~/.local/share/GXDE/gxde-k9/logs/)
    with size limit and clear-on-startup; new --log-dir/--log-max-size/--no-logs.
  * Add gxde-k9-chocker entry: list/show/add/remove/import tasks,
    interactive menu and script-friendly subcommands; manage user-side configs
    and (with privilege escalation + risk warning) system-side configs.
  * Support importing external scripts as .slimy/.shot/etc.

